Describe a person who often buys at the street market at cheaper prices.
- Who he/she is
- How you knew her
- What he/she usually buys
- Explain how you feel about this person

I’d like to talk about my mother, who is probably one of the most cost-conscious people I know, especially when it comes to shopping at street markets. Her name is Hoa, and she’s in her 50s, although she looks younger than her age. She works as a farmer and has been doing this for over 20 years.

When I was younger, I often went to the market with her, and that’s how I learned about her shopping habits. There’s a small street market near our house, just a five-minute walk away, and she used to go there almost every day to buy fresh food and household items. Over time, she became very familiar with the prices and the vendors, so she was rarely overcharged.

What really stands out about her is her bargaining skill. She knows exactly how to negotiate and often manages to get things at much lower prices. I still remember one time, when I was younger, we visited a market while traveling and found a coat that I really liked. The original price was quite high, but after a short negotiation, she managed to get it for nearly half the price, which really impressed me.

I believe the reason she always shops this way is that she wants to save as much money as possible for the family. Since there are many daily expenses, she has to manage the budget carefully.

I truly admire her for being so practical and responsible. Thanks to her, I’ve also learned the value of money and how to spend wisely. I feel very grateful to have a mother like her, and I hope she stays healthy and happy for many years to come.
